description:
G. Braziller | 1992 | Pdf | Eng, Fra | ISBN:10 080761291X | 104 pag | 6.62 MB

The original was produced in the early forties as a limited edition commissioned by the original publisher, Teriade in Paris. Matisse was laid up in bed after an operation, but he could still produce art in the form of cut paper compositions from painted paper, and these compositions make up the theater and circus themes of his book, "Jazz". The text was handled by the publisher, but was handwritten and inserted as directed by Matisse
